helet nicht zur Verzweiflung oder in Krisen, sondern bildet die Grundlage dafür, das Leben mit Freude als eine Gabe Gottes annehmen zu können. Die damit rekonstruierte Denkfigur hat nicht nur für die anthropologischen und theologischen Linien innerhalb der Hebräischen Bibel hohe Relevanz, sondern kann auch theologischen Diskursen der Gegenwart weiterführende Impulse geben.  aKohelet was one of the great thinkers of ancient Judah. His empirical studies led him to the insight that, although there is no permanence for man, that is no reason for resignation. Instead, the present can be understood as a scope of action given to man by God. This volume elucidates the anthropological and theological profile of this work with a complete interpretation and by providing helpful contextualization.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAnthropologie. 4aKohelet. 4aTheologie. 4aWeisheitsliteratur. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aAnthropology.  aKohelet.  aTheology.  aWisdom Literature.1 aSaur, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831111972100 cprintz978311119560540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311119719740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111197197423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111197197/original  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023